id Secrecy Found in Papal Elections |journal=The Catholic Historical Review |date=2003a|oclc=222885361|volume=89 |pages=165-181 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Baumgartner|first=F. J.|title=Behind Locked Doors: A History of the Papal Elections|year=2003b|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|location=Basingstoke|isbn=978-1-13711-014-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Beck |first1=A. |title=The Rise and Fall of Catholic Sweden |journal=Studies: An Irish Quarterly Review |date=1940 |pages=382-394 |ref=harv |oclc=220720325}}\n* {{cite web |last1=Benedictine Charter |title=Ohannes Berardi , Chartularium Monasterii Casauriensis, Ordinis S. Benedicti. |url=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b84526553/f517.item |website=Gallica/BnF |accessdate=11 April 2020 |ref=harv |archiveurl=https://archive.is/aMk8F |archivedate=11 April 2020 |date=2020}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bergquist|first=A.|editor-last1=Bolton|editor-first1=B.|editor-last2=Duggan|editor-first2=A.|title=Adrian IV, the English Pope, 1154\u20131159: Studies and Texts|year=2003|publisher=Ashgate|location=Aldershot|isbn=978-0-75460-708-3|page=41\u201348|chapter=The Papal Legate: Nicholas Breakspear's Scandinavian Mission|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Birk|first=J. C.|title=Norman Kings of Sicily and the Rise of the Anti-Islamic Critique: Baptized Sultans|year=2016|publisher=PalgraveMacmillan|location=Cham|isbn=978-3-31947-041-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Birkett|first=H.|editor-last=Boardman|editor-first1=S.|editor-last2=Williamson|editor-first2=E.|title=The Cult of Saints and the Virgin Mary in Medieval Scotland|series=Studies in Celtic History|volume=28|year=2010|publisher=Boydell & Brewer|location=Woodbridge|isbn=978-1-84383-562-2|page=4360|chapter= The Struggle for Sanctity: St Waltheof of Melrose, Cistercian in-house Cults and Canonisation Procedure at the Turn of the Thirteenth Century|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Blumenthal|first=U.|editor-last1=Luscombe|editor-first1=D.|editor-last2=Riley-Smith|editor-first2=