drawa]] (Offensive Line)\n*Matt Barnes (Special Teams Coordinator / Asst. Secondary)\n*Corey Dennis (Senior Quality Control - Offense)\n*Chandler Whitmer (Graduate Assistant - Offense)\n*Trey Holtz (Graduate Assistant - Offense)\n*Kenny Anunike (Graduate Assistant - Defense)\n*Sean Duggan (Graduate Assistant - Defense)\n*Keenan Bailey (Quality Control Coach - Offense)\n*Parker Fleming (Quality Control Coach - Special Teams)\n*Matt Thurin (Quality Control Coach - Defense)\n*Drew Christ (Quality Control Coach - Defense)\n*[[Mickey Marotti]] (Assistant Athletic Director / Director of Football)\n}}\n\n===Coaching changes===\n\n*On December 4, 2018, Head Coach [[Urban Meyer]] announced his retirement from coaching effective after the [[2019 Rose Bowl]] Game. Ryan Day was announced as his replacement.<ref>{{cite web |title=Urban Meyer to retire after Rose Bowl, with Ryan Day taking over as Buckeyes head coach |url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/25449933/ohio-state-buckeyes-head-coach-urban-meyer-retire-coaching-rose-bowl |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n*On December 8, 2018, Interim Wide Receivers Coach [[Brian Hartline]] was promoted to full-time Wide Receivers coach.<ref>{{cite web |title=Buckeyes' Ryan Day promotes Brian Hartline to full-time WR coach |url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/25483969/brian-hartline-promoted-full-position-ohio-state-buckeyes-receivers-coach |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n*On January 2, 2019, [[Oklahoma State Cowboys football|Oklahoma State]] Offensive Coordinator [[Mike Yurcich]] was hired by Ohio State as the new Passing Game Coordinator and [[Quarterback|Quarterbacks]] coach.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ohio State officially announces Mike Yurcich as new QB coach |url=https://247sports.com/college/ohio-state/Article/Mike-Yurcich-Ohio-State-Buckeyes-passing-game-coordinator-and-quarterbacks-coach-127238787/ |website=247sports.com |publisher=247 Sports |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n*On January 4, 2019, Ohio State Co-Defensive Coordinator and Safeties coach [[Alex Grinch]] was hired by [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]] as Defensive Coordinator.<ref>{{cite web |title=Alex Grinch leaves Ohio State for Oklahoma |url=https://247sports.com/college/ohio-state/Article/Alex-Grinch-leaves-Ohio-State-Buckeyes-football-for-Oklahoma-Sooners-127316331/ |website=247sports.com |publisher=247 Sports |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n*On January 7, 2019, Defensive Coordinator [[Greg Schiano]] and [[Linebacker|Linebackers]] Coach [[Billy Davis (American football coach)|Billy Davis]] were fired by Ohio State, and replaced with [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]] Defensive line coach [[Greg Mattison]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Sources: Greg Schiano out as DC; Greg Mattison coming to OSU |url=https://247sports.com/college/ohio-state/Article/Ohio-State-Buckeyes-football-Greg-Schiano-out-as-defensive-coordinator-Greg-Mattison-coming-to-OSU-127454837/ |website=247Sports.com |publisher=247 Sports |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref> and former [[San Francisco 49ers]] Defensive backs coach [[Jeff Hafley]].<ref>{{cite web |title=OHIO STATE HIRES FORMER 49ERS DEFENSIVE BACKS COACH JEFF HAFLEY AS CO-DEFENSIVE COORDINATOR |url=https://www.elevenwarriors.com/ohio-state-football/2019/01/101415/ohio-state-will-hire-former-49ers-defensive-backs-coach-jeff-hafley-as-co-defensive-coordinator-according-to-pete |website=elevenwarriors.com |publisher=ELEVEN WARRIORS |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref> Mattison and Hafley will serve as Co-Defensive Coordinators.\n*Also On January 7, 2019, Defensive Line Coach [[Larry Johnson (American football coach)|Larry Johnson]] was promoted to Associate Head Coach, while continuing his duties as defensive line coach, he takes over for former Associate Head Coach [[Greg Schiano]] who was fired earlier that day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Larry Johnson receives promotion from Ohio State |url=https://247sports.com/college/ohio-state/Article/Ohio-State-Buckeyes-football-Larry-Johnson-receives-promotion-127463851/ |website=247sports.com |publisher=247 Sports |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n*On January 8, 2019, Ohio State hired Michigan Linebackers Coach [[Al Washington (coach)|Al Washington]] as the new Linebackers coach.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ohio State to hire Al Washington away from Michigan |url=https://247sports.com/college/ohio-state/Article/Ohio-State-Buckeyes-football-hire-Al-Washington-away-from-Michigan-Wolverines-127508869/ |website=247sports.com |publisher=247 Sports |accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Rankings==\n{{Further|2019 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings}}\n{{NCAA Division I FBS CFP ranking movements\n| year            = {{2019}}\n| finalpollweek   = 16\n| cfpfirstweek    = 10\n| AP_pre          = 5\n| coaches_pre     = 5\n| AP_1            = 5\n| coaches_1       = 5\n| AP_2            = 6\n| coaches_2       = 6\n| AP_3            = 6\n| coaches_3       = 6\n| AP_4            = 5\n| coaches_4       = 6\n| AP_5            = 4 <small>(7)</small>\n| coaches_5       = 5 <small>(4)</small>\n| AP_6            = 3<small>T</small><small>(10)</small>\n| coaches_6       = 4 <small>(3)</small>\n| AP_7            = 4 <small>(9)</small>\n| coaches_7       = 4 <small>(4)</small>\n| AP_8            = 3 <small>(13)</small>\n| coaches_8       = 4 <small>(8)</small>\n| AP_9            = 3 <small>(17)</small>\n| coaches_9       = 4 <small>(8)</small>\n| AP_10           = 3 <small>(17)</small>\n| coaches_10      = 4 <small>(8)</small>\n| cfp_10          = 1\n| AP_11           = 2 <small>(5)</small>\n| coaches_11      = 2 <small>(5)</small>\n| cfp_11          = 2 \n| AP_12           = 2 <small>(5)</small>\n| coaches_12      = 2 <small>(6)</small>\n| cfp_12          = 2\n| AP_13           = 2 <small>(9)</small>\n| coaches_13      = 2 <small>(7)</small>\n| cfp_13          = 1\n| AP_14           = 2 <small>(19)</small>\n| coaches_14      = 2 <small>(17)