Hears a Who!]]'' || Wickersham Brother ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Phantom Tollbooth (film)|The Phantom Tollbooth]]'' || Lethargians ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Aristocats]]'' || Billy Bass - Russian Cat || Voice\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1971 || ''[[The Cat in the Hat (TV special)|The Cat in the Hat]]'' || Thing One || Voice\n|-\n| ''[[Bedknobs and Broomsticks]]'' || Singing voice of Russian vendor / Various cartoon animal voices ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1972 || ''[[Snoopy, Come Home]]'' || Singer of \"No Dogs Allowed\" || Voice\n|-\n| ''[[The Lorax (TV special)|The Lorax]]'' || Singer || Voice\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 1977 || ''[[The Hobbit (1977 film)|The Hobbit]]'' || Goblins/Chorus || Voice\n|-\n| ''[[Halloween Is Grinch Night]]'' || Singer / Monsters || Voice\n|-\n| ''[[Donny & Marie (1976 TV series)|Donny & Marie]]'' || [[Darth Vader]] / Narrator || ''[[Star Wars]]'' Segment\n|-\n| 1978 || ''[[The Small One]]'' || Potter ||\n|-\n| 1979 || ''[[Rudolph and Frosty's Christmas in July]]'' || Genie of the Ice Scepter || Voice\n|-\n| 1980 || ''[[The Return of the King (1980 film)|The Return of the King]]'' || Goblins/Chorus || Voice, Uncredited\n|-\n| 1987 || ''[[The Brave Little Toaster (film)|The Brave Little Toaster]]'' || Kirby || Voice\n|-\n| 1990 || ''[[Disney Sing-Along Songs|Disney Sing Along Songs: Disneyland Fun \u2013 It's a Small World]]'' || Singer of \"[[Grim Grinning Ghosts]]\" ||\n|-\n| 1996 || ''Superior Duck'' || The Narrator ||\n|-\n| 1997 || ''[[The Brave Little Toaster to the Rescue]]'' ||rowspan=\"2\"| Kirby ||rowspan=\"2\"| Voice; Final films\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[The Brave Little Toaster Goes to Mars]]''\n|}\n\n===Commercials===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| late 1970s-early 1980s || ''[[Toys R Us]]'' || Geoffrey the Giraffe\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 1953\u20132005 ||''[[Kellogg's Frosted Flakes]]'' || [[Tony the Tiger]]\n|}\n\n==Partial solo discography==\n{{div col|colwidth=26em}}\n*''Mad, Baby, Mad'' \u2013 1955 (Fabor)\n*